thm 2reu7(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, wff w0) {

  -| diffss(s0, s1)

  -| diffsc(s1, c1)

  a1ii(wb(wa(wreu(s0, c0, wrex(s1, c1, w0)), wreu(s1, c1, wrex(s0, c0, w0))), wreu(s0, c0, wreu(s1, c1, wa(wrex(s0, c0, w0), wrex(s1, c1, w0))))), diffss(s0, s1))

  reubii(s0, c0, wreu(s1, c1, wa(wrex(s0, c0, w0), wrex(s1, c1, w0))), wa(wreu(s1, c1, wrex(s0, c0, w0)), wrex(s1, c1, w0)))
  3bitri(wreu(s1, c1, wa(wrex(s0, c0, w0), wrex(s1, c1, w0))), wa(wreu(s1, c1, wrex(s0, c0, w0)), wrex(s1, c1, w0)), wreu(s1, c1, wa(wrex(s1, c1, w0), wrex(s0, c0, w0))), wa(wrex(s1, c1, w0), wreu(s1, c1, wrex(s0, c0, w0))))

blocks.name: 2reu8
blocks.content: Two equivalent expressions for double restricted existential uniqueness, analogous to ~ 2eu8 . Curiously, we can put ` E! ` on either of the internal conjuncts but not both. We can also commute ` E! x e. A E! y e. B ` using ~ 2reu7 . (Contributed by Alexander van der Vekens, 2-Jul-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm 2reu8(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, wff w0) {

  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
} = {
  3bitr3ri(wreu(s0, c0, wreu(s1, c1, wa(wrex(s0, c0, w0), wrex(s1, c1, w0)))), wreu(s0, c0, wreu(s1, c1, wa(wreu(s0, c0, w0), wrex(s1, c1, w0)))), wa(wreu(s0, c0, wrex(s1, c1, w0)), wreu(s1, c1, wreu(s0, c0, w0))), wa(wreu(s0, c0, wrex(s1, c1, w0)), wreu(s1, c1, wrex(s0, c0, w0))))

  reuan(s0, c0, wreu(s1, c1, wreu(s0, c0, w0)), wrex(s1, c1, w0))
  nfreu(s0, s1, c1, wreu(s0, c0, w0))

  reubii(s0, c0, wreu(s1, c1, wa(wreu(s0, c0, w0), wrex(s1, c1, w0))), wa(wreu(s1, c1, wreu(s0, c0, w0)), wrex(s1, c1, w0)))
  3bitri(wreu(s1, c1, wa(wreu(s0, c0, w0), wrex(s1, c1, w0))), wa(wreu(s1, c1, wreu(s0, c0, w0)), wrex(s1, c1, w0)), wreu(s1, c1, wa(wrex(s1, c1, w0), wreu(s0, c0, w0))), wa(wrex(s1, c1, w0), wreu(s1, c1, wreu(s0, c0, w0))))
